spec: as3241
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(asyncio)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 663 (as3241): __rtruediv__, __rfloordiv__, __rmod__ dict-presence (reflected division/modulo) for asyncio types."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: asyncio.Task, asyncio.Future, asyncio.Event, asyncio.Lock, asyncio.Semaphore, asyncio.BoundedSemaphore, asyncio.Condition, asyncio.Queue, asyncio.PriorityQueue, asyncio.LifoQueue."
    - "Key finding (__rtruediv__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __rtruediv__. Reflected true division (__rtruediv__) is invoked when the left operand's __truediv__ returns NotImplemented — for example, n / obj triggers obj.__rtruediv__(n) if int's __truediv__ does not handle obj. asyncio types define no __truediv__ (confirmed false in wave 659), so __rtruediv__ is equally absent. asyncio types are coroutine-based concurrency primitives — not numeric types. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition are boolean-state synchronization objects; n / event is not a defined Python expression. asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore manage a permit counter entirely through acquire()/release() coroutines; the counter is not exposed for division. asyncio.Task/Future are pending coroutine result handles; reflected division is undefined for them. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue are ordered item stores with no numeric data model."
    - "Key finding (__rfloordiv__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __rfloordiv__. Reflected floor division (__rfloordiv__) is the mirror of __floordiv__; it is invoked when the left operand's __floordiv__ returns NotImplemented. asyncio types define no __floordiv__ (confirmed false in wave 659), so __rfloordiv__ is also absent. No asyncio type exposes a floor-division interface from either side of the operator."
    - "Key finding (__rmod__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __rmod__. Reflected modulo (__rmod__) is invoked when the left operand's __mod__ returns NotImplemented. asyncio types define no __mod__ (confirmed false in wave 659), so __rmod__ is equally absent. asyncio.Queue is an ordered item store but does not support % format-string interpolation the way str does (str.__rmod__ handles the % operator for string formatting). asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore manage a permit counter but expose no modulo interface. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition/Task/Future have no arithmetic semantics of any kind."
    - "Continues the all-false pattern from wave 662 (__radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__). asyncio is a pure coroutine concurrency library; its types interact exclusively through await, async with, async for, and explicit method calls — never through Python's arithmetic data model, including reflected division and modulo."
    - "Cross-wave summary for asyncio subjects:"
    - "  Wave 652 (as3076): __get__ — Task/Future/Queue/Handle true; others false."
    - "  Wave 653 (as3091): __hash__/__eq__/__bool__ — selected true."
    - "  Wave 654 (as3106): __lt__/__le__/__gt__ — TimerHandle true; others false."
    - "  Wave 655 (as3121): __ge__ — TimerHandle true; __repr__ — 12 classes true."
    - "  Wave 656 (as3136): __call__/__len__/__getitem__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 657 (as3151): __setitem__/__delitem__/__contains__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 658 (as3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 659 (as3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 660 (as3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 661 (as3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 662 (as3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 663 (as3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 10."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __rtruediv__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__rtruediv__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __rtruediv__.
# Reflected true division (__rtruediv__) is invoked when the left operand's
#   __truediv__ returns NotImplemented — e.g., n / obj triggers obj.__rtruediv__(n).
# asyncio types define no __truediv__ (confirmed false in wave 659), so
#   __rtruediv__ is equally absent.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: boolean-state synchronization guards;
#   n / event is not a defined Python expression.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: permit-counter objects; the counter is
#   fully encapsulated behind acquire()/release() coroutines.
# asyncio.Task/Future: pending coroutine result handles; reflected division
#   is undefined for them.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: ordered item stores with no numeric
#   or division semantics of any kind.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table as3241.rtruediv:
  description: "asyncio types __rtruediv__ dict-presence checks; wave 663"
  kind: python_call_eq
