# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __rmod__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__rmod__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __rmod__.
# Reflected modulo (__rmod__) is invoked when the left operand's __mod__
#   returns NotImplemented — e.g., n % obj triggers obj.__rmod__(n).
# asyncio types define no __mod__ (confirmed false in wave 659), so __rmod__
#   is equally absent.
# asyncio.Queue: an ordered item store but does NOT support % format-string
#   interpolation the way str does (str defines __rmod__ to handle the
#   % formatting operator from the right). asyncio.Queue is not a string type.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: permit-counter types with no modulo
#   semantics exposed through any part of their API.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: boolean-state synchronization objects;
#   n % event is not a defined Python expression.
# asyncio.Task/Future: pending result handles; reflected modulo is undefined.
# asyncio.PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: queue subclasses with the same absence of
#   arithmetic semantics as Queue.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

